.rule_6_6_3_ensure_idle_timeout_is_set_for_all_login_classes

Reference: Juniper Networks (http://www.juniper.net/techpubs/en_US/junos9.5/information-
products/topic-collections/swconfig-system-basics/frameset.html)

Remediation: Configure the Idle Timeout for a class using the following command under the [edit
system login] hierarchy:
[edit system login]
user@host#set class <class name> idle-timeout <timeout in minutes>




